terminal extramedullary conus spinal cord lipoma
definition: A rare form of extramedullary conus region spinal cord lipoma characterized by its location, extending from the poorly delineated tip of the conus.

label: transitional extramedullary conus spinal cord lipoma
definition: A rare form of extramedullary conus region spinal cord lipoma characterized by a location at the posterior surface of the conus and its tip. i.e-\transitional\" between posterior and terminal conus region spinal cord lipoma."

label: posterior extramedullary conus spinal cord lipoma
definition: A rare form of conus region spinal cord lipoma characterized by its location where the interface between the lipoma and the spinal cord is strictcly above the level of the tip of the conus. The tip of the conus is readily delineated.

label: lipomatous non-saccular limited dorsal myeloschisis
definition: A rare non-saccular limited dorsal myeloschisis histologically characterized by skin tissue with a jagged depression of squamous epithelium continued to subcutaneous mature adipose tissue with loose connective tissue. GFAP-immunopositive glial cells are embedded in the subcutaneous lipoma. The extradural and intradural stalk have cord-like fibrocollagenous tissue containing adipose tissue, peripheral nerve fibers, clusters of melanocytes, and skeletal muscle fibers.

label: fibroneural non-saccular limited dorsal myeloschisis
definition: A rare non-saccular limited dorsal myeloschisis, in which the stalk histology is characterized by skin tissue with dermo-epidermal epithelium in continuity with a subcutaneous fibrocollagenous tract containing various ectopic tissues.

label: terminal myelocystocele
definition: A rare closed spinal dysraphism characterized by a myelocystocele at the termination of the spinal cord. It may be an isolated anomaly or be associated with other defects, including sacral agenesis, anorectal and genitourinary anomalies. The conus is not identifiable. The myelocystocele sac may have a significant lipomatous component (terminal lipomyelocystocele).

label: saccular limited dorsal myeloschisis
definition: A rare form of limited dorsal myeloschisis (LDM), characterized by the stalk attached to the apex of a fully epithelialized meningocele. Chiari II malformation is not present.

label: myelic limited dorsal malformation
definition: A rare intermediate form of open dysraphism between myelomeningocele and saccular limited dorsal myeloschisis without fulfilling the characteristics of one of these two diagnosis, characterized by stretched neurulated spinal cord attached at the dome of a sac. Partial cerebral signs of open dysraphism can be observed and the meningocele is usually poorly epithelialized.

dysplasia of the proximal femoral epiphyses
definition: A developmental disorder affecting the growth and development of the proximal end of the femur (thigh bone) near the hip joint characterized by avascular necrosis of the femoral head, cystic changes of the femoral head, and/or sclerosis of the femoral head. It is a relatively milder form of the other skeletal disorders associated with COL2A1.
